# Domain Spec Sync With Data Model

When changing domain/data model structures, always keep conceptual specs and domain-sync checker artifacts synchronized in the same change set.

## Trigger (must update conceptual specs)

Apply this whenever a change affects conceptual intent in `backend/app/model/**`, including:

- entity added, removed, or renamed
- relationship/cardinality changed
- ownership/context semantics changed
- lifecycle/invariant semantics changed

## Required updates

- Update the relevant focused diagram(s) in `spec/domain/*-domain.puml`.
- Update `spec/domain/gen-domain.puml` for cross-domain impacts.
- Update `spec/domain/gen-paths-domain.puml` when user/business journeys (`P1..P6`) change.
- Keep `spec/domain/domain-sync-mapping.json` aligned (aliases, ignored conceptual edges, tracked entities).
- Keep `spec/domain/README.md` aligned when files, checker behavior, or scope change.
- Keep checker code aligned if needed: `qa/spec_tools/check_domain_sync.py`.
- Update docs when checker usage/behavior changes:
  - `doc/specification-manual.qmd` (primary)
  - references in `doc/database-manual.qmd`, `doc/test-manual.qmd`, `doc/diy-manual.qmd`

## Required verification

For model/concept changes, run:

```bash
cd /Users/stephan/Workspace/TPL-App/backend
source .venv/bin/activate
cd /Users/stephan/Workspace/TPL-App
python -m qa.spec_tools.check_domain_sync
```

If the check fails, fix diagrams/mapping/model before finishing.

## Completion gate

Do not finish model-affecting work unless:

- conceptual specs are updated (or an explicit no-change rationale is documented), and
- the domain sync checker passes.

